description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results of the NYSE® FactSet® Global Robotics and Artificial Intelligence Index.
 The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The underlying index measures the performance of equity securities issued by companies involved in robotics and artificial intelligence activities.
